prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "A user can create an account.",
      "evidence_quote": "A user can either create an account or continue to the video section directly."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "After creating an account, a user can watch videos.",
      "evidence_quote": "If the user creates an account, they can then move forward to watch videos."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A user can upload videos.",
      "evidence_quote": "The user can also upload videos and then view them."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A user can save videos in their likes list while viewing videos.",
      "evidence_quote": "While viewing videos, the user may either finish there or save videos in their likes list."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A user can view their saved videos in the likes list.",
      "evidence_quote": "If videos are saved in the likes list, the user can view that list and then upload videos based on those liked videos."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A user can enter a discussion option.",
      "evidence_quote": "If the user enters the discussion option, the discussion takes place and then ends."
    }
  ]
}

llm_response:
```json
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "A user can create an account.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow a user to create an account."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "After creating an account, a user can watch videos.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall enable a user to watch videos after they have created an account."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "A user can upload videos.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall permit a user to upload videos."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "A user can save videos in their likes list while viewing videos.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow a user to save videos in their likes list during video viewing."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "A user can view their saved videos in the likes list.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall enable a user to view their saved videos from the likes list."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "A user can enter a discussion option.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow a user to enter the discussion option."
    }
  ]
}
```
